    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require police to keep their body worn cameras on when dealing with people",
        "additional_details": "I think this should apply to interactions in houses, hospitals or custody suites. Any officer who fails should be sanctioned.",
        "background": "I would like it to become mandatory that all body worn cameras are switched on when police are interacting with people. I think they should be switched on before an officer leaves their vehicle and shouldn't be turned off until the officer has left the person/persons they're dealing with. ",
